    "body": "The `Compiler.Nodes.relative_position` simply chops off the first `len(os.path.abspath(os.getcwd()))` characters from the file name. This is of course completely wrong if the source file is in the search path and not relative to cwd.\n\nExample project:\n```\n.\n├── build.sh\n└── src\n    ├── A\n    │   ├── test.pyx\n    └── B\n        └── test01234567890123456789012345678901234567890123456789.pxi\n```\nwith files\n```\n$ cat build.sh\ncython -I src --embed-positions src/A/test.pyx\n\n$ cat src/A/test.pyx\ninclude 'B/test01234567890123456789012345678901234567890123456789.pxi'\nfoo()\n\n$ cat src/B/test01234567890123456789012345678901234567890123456789.pxi \ndef foo():\n    \"\"\"\n    foo docstring\n    \"\"\"\n```\nThen the emitted source position information for the included file is truncated:\n```\n$ ./build.sh  && grep File: src/A/test.c \nstatic char __pyx_k_1[= \"File: src/A/test.pyx (starting at line 3)\";\nstatic char __pyx_doc_4test_foo[](]) = \"File: 890123456789.pxi (starting at line 3)\\n\\n    foo docstring\\n    \";\n```\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/817",
